(* README *)

1 - Description
    -----------

    T000 provides a mechanized proof of the pigeonhole divisibility theorem
    in Rocq.  The result states that any subset A of {1, ..., 2n} with
    |A| = n + 1 contains two distinct elements a and b such that a | b or
    b | a.

    The proof factors into three parts: an odd-part decomposition showing
    that each element of {1, ..., 2n} maps to one of n odd categories, a
    pigeonhole argument producing two elements with the same odd part, and
    an arithmetic lemma showing that shared odd parts force divisibility.

    This development serves as the canonical style example for Proofcase.
    The conventions follow the Canonicalization appendix.


2 - Repository Tree
    ---------------

    .
    ├── README
    │
    │      (This file.)
    │
    ├── R00__Odd_Part.v
    │
    │      Odd-part decomposition of positive integers.  We define the
    │      odd_part and val2 functions, prove that odd_part is odd, divides
    │      the original, and that same odd parts force divisibility.  We
    │      also define odd_range n (the n odd numbers in {1, ..., 2n}) and
    │      show it has length n and receives every odd_part image.
    │
    └── R01__Pigeonhole_Divisibility.v

           Main theorem.  We state a list-based pigeonhole principle and
           apply it with the odd-part map to conclude that any (n+1)-element
           subset of {1, ..., 2n} contains a divisibility pair.
